    author: 'Skye Gyngell',
    about: 'Sweet tasting, packed full of goodness and sustaining enough to carry you through until lunchtime, it works a treat. The original recipe dates back to the 1890s and was created by Swiss Dr Bircher-Benner',
    ingredients: ['whole rolled oats 250g', 'grated zest of 1 lemon', '100ml water', '2 sharp green dessert apples', '500g plain yoghurt', '100ml runny honey', '2tbsp chopped and toasted nuts', 'Large handful of summer berries or 4-6 tbsp of poached autumn fruits'],
